title: Prep Roundup: Sequoyah wins twice at county
text: Prep Roundup: Sequoyah wins twice at county by Tribune staff reports Cherokee Tribune October 02, 2015 12:00 AM | 355 views | 0 | 2 | | Sequoyah earned a sweep on the first day of the county championship, beating Cherokee (25-14, 25-23) and River Ridge (25-20, 25-21) on Thursday at the War Lodge.Kelley Hartman had 20 kills, two blocks and two aces for the Lady Chiefs (16-11), while sister Lauren added 15 kills, 15 digs and two blocks. Annika Lanning contributed 43 assists, seven digs and three aces. Karen Morris had 24 digs and Mallory Lawson chipped in with 15 digs and two aces. Deja Goss totaled seven kills and two blocks.Sequoyah will close out the round-robin event at Cherokee on Saturday, facing Etowah, Woodstock and Cherokee. Share This Article | similar stories
